The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 November is 98,521 (11,355.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 November, there were 3,990 new confirmed cases (459.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 October, there were 4,756 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (766 fewer cases).
